      • printOutOrSaveKNSNCounts

        public static <T,V> void printOutOrSaveKNSNCounts(java.lang.String name,
                                                  java.util.HashMap<T,java.util.HashMap<V,java.lang.Long>> tuplesMap,
                                                  java.util.HashMap<T,java.lang.Long[]> KNSNCountsMap,
                                                  long[] allKNSNCounts,
                                                  boolean word2IsTheFeature,
                                                  boolean word1TypeIsParaphrase,
                                                  boolean printOutKNSNCounts)
        This function is used for printing out the KNS N counts for words and features. In case of words it is used in a way that it first accumulates all the information from all feature types, and only then printes them out. In case of features, there is no need for information accumulation, so everything is printed out staight away.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of keys in @param tuplesMap
        V - the type of keys in the HashMaps inside @param tuplesMap
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the information to be printed out
        tuplesMap - the map containing the (word, feature) pairs
        KNSNCountsMap - the map in which the KNSNCounts for the words are accumulated
        allKNSNCounts - the array in which the allKNSNCounts for the given POS are accumulated
        word2IsTheFeature - a boolean denoting whether the keys in the HashMaps inside @param tuplesMap are features (or words)
        word1TypeIsParaphrase - a boolean denoting whether the keys in @param tuplesMap are of the type Paraphrase (or String)
        printOutKNSNCounts - a boolean denoting whether the accumulated information should be printed out
